Mechel, Rosneft, HMS, Polyus: Russia Stock Market Preview

-- B y   A n n a   S h i r y a e v s k a y a
-- 
2011-06-06T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/mechel-rosneft-hms-polyus-russia-stock-market-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and share
prices are from the previous close in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  was little changed at 1,633.49.
The dollar-denominated RTS Index gained 0.4 percent to 1,865.64.  OAO  Mechel (MTLR)  : Mechel will close the book on 10
billion rubles ($359.4 million) of bonds. Russia’s largest
producer of coal for steelmaking fell 2.6 percent to 725.60
rubles.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX): Crude oil fell for a second day in
 New York  on speculation that fuel demand is faltering along with
economic growth, and as OPEC ministers arrive in Vienna to
discuss production targets. Russia’s biggest oil producer rose 1
percent to 237.64 rubles.       HMS Hydraulic Machines & Systems Group Plc (HMSG LI): The
Russian pump maker that sold shares to the public in February is
due to publish first-quarter financial results. HMS Group
advanced 0.6 percent to $7.90 in  London .  OAO Polyus Gold (PLZL RX): Gold rose to a five-week high on
speculation that borrowing costs in the U.S. will remain low as
a faltering recovery erodes the value of the dollar and boosts
the appeal of precious metals. Russia’s biggest miner of the
metal fell 0.7 percent to 1,978.60 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anna Shiryaevskaya in Moscow at 
 ashiryaevska@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
